narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You're required to take this to get L1 credit. It's enjoyable. Pick a good teacher. Just shop around, you can't really go wrong with the Italian department.

Italian 120 is definitely a good class to take if you enjoyed Italian 110, but keep in mind that it is a lot more work and much more is expected of you. Your compositions are graded much more critically, and the grammar keeps building upon simpler grammar, thus becoming harder and harder. Be prepared to work hard.
If languages come easily to you, I definitely recommend this class. If not, stick with the language you took in high school.
